The paper deals with the computation of the weighted Moore-Penrose inverse of multiple-variable polynomial matrices, which involves symbolic computation and numerical algorithms. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories, including cs.SC (Symbolic Computation), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.SY (Systems and Control), cs.NA (Numerical Analysis), and cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science). Among these, cs.SC and cs.DS are the most likely categories, as the paper focuses on the development of algorithms and their implementation in a symbolic computational package. The other categories are also possible, as the paper deals with numerical computations and control systems.
